Preheat the oven to 200°C. Put a large pan of water on to boil with @salt{0.5%tsp}. Peel the @potatoes{450%g} and thinly slice into 1/2 cm rounds. When the water is boiling, add the potato and cook until just tender ~{7-8%minutes}. Once cooked, drain the potatoes in a #colander{}.

Trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}. Halve lengthways, then thinly slice widthways. Trim the @carrot{1}, then quarter lengthways (no need to peel). Chop widthways into small pieces. Pick the @rosemary{1}(leaves picked and finely chopped) and finely chop (discard the stalks). Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Chop the @French Camembert{250%g} into 2cm chunks and set aside.

Heat a splash of @?olive oil{} in a large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the leek, carrot and @sliced mushrooms{150%g} and cook stirring continuously until soft and starting to brown, ~{5-6%minutes}. Next, add the @shredded Savoy cabbage{100%g} and cook until wilted, ~{3-4%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Stir in the garlic and half the rosemary, cook for ~{1%minute}. Meanwhile mix the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g}, remaining rosemary and @olive oil{1%tbsp} (see ingredients for amount). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the @water{100%ml}, @wild mushroom paste{1} and @reduced fat creme fraiche{112.5%g} to the pan, stir well and bring to a boil. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Transfer the vegetable filling into an #ovenproof dish{} (we used a 20x20 cm dish for 2 people). Layer the potato discs on top (careful they may be hot!) Scatter over the Camembert chunks. Sprinkle over the rosemary crumb mix. Bake on the top shelf of your oven until the cheese melts and the hotpot starts to bubble, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Carefully take the hotpot out of the oven and share among your plates. Sprinkle over the @truffle zest{1} for add an extra flavour boost. Enjoy!

> Don't worry if one or two of your potato discs break up a little when layering, it will not affect your finished dish!